  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>The meanings of σῴζω and σωτηρία in this subdomain differ from the meaning of ἐξαιρέομαι ({D:21.17}) in implying not only a rescue from danger but a restoration to a former state of safety and well being. It is this aspect of the terms σῴζω and σωτηρία which provides such an excellent basis for their use in denoting religious salvation.</Content>
    </Note>
